            <td class="blob-code"><span class="hljs-attr">    access_control:</span></td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="35"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">        <span class="hljs-comment"># - { path: ^/admin, roles: ROLE_ADMIN }</span></td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>And open up <code>GenusAdminController</code>. To check if the current user has a role,
you'll always use one service: the authorization checker. It looks like this:
<code>if (!$this-&gt;get('security.authorization_checker')-&gt;isGranted('ROLE_ADMIN')</code>. So,
if we do <em>not</em> have <code>ROLE_ADMIN</code>, then <code>throw $this-&gt;createAccessDeniedException()</code>:</p>
