<p>It turns out - no matter <em>where</em> you are - if you need to deny access for any reason,
just throw this exception. Symfony handles everything else.</p>
<h2 id="deny-access-the-short-way">Deny Access (the short way)! <a class="headerlink" href="deny-access-inside-controller#deny-access-the-short-way" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
