<h2 id="locking-down-an-entire-controller">Locking down an Entire Controller <a class="headerlink" href="deny-access-inside-controller#locking-down-an-entire-controller" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But no matter how easy we make it, what we <em>really</em> want to do is lock down this
<em>entire</em> controller. Right now, we could still go to <code>/admin/genus/new</code> and have
access. We <em>could</em> repeat the security check in every controller... or we could do
something cooler.</p>
<p>Add the annotation <em>above</em> the class itself:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="030dbd2c2d">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
